-- GDF Suez Seeks E.ON Stake to Take Majority of Gasag, FT Deutschland Says
-- Angela Cullen
-- 2010-04-26T05:31:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/gdf-suez-seeks-e-on-stake-to-take-majority-of-gasag-ft-deutschland-says.html

          
          
             GDF Suez is in early talks to
purchase E.ON AG’s 37 percent share of Gasag Berliner Gaswerke
AG as it seeks to obtain a majority holding in the Berlin
utility, Financial Times Deutschland reported, citing
unidentified people close the French company.  
 The acquisition, which would take GDF’s share to 69
percent, may be valued at as much as 800 million euros ($1.07
billion), the newspaper said.  
          
          


  


        